   25. Put the following lines of code in order to create a function that returns the number of bits needed to store an image. Assume that each pixel is represented by 24 bits.
   -----
   def image_size(img):
   '''Returns the size of an image in bits'''
   =====
       numbits = img.getWidth() * img.getHeight() * 24
   =====
       return numbits